interface Light{
    void switchOn();
    void switchoff();
}

interface fan{
    void startFan();
    void stopFan();
}

class SmartRoom extends Light,fan{
  public  void switchoff(){
        System.out.println("The Light in the Room is Off");
    }
   public void switchOn(){
       System.out.println("The Light in the Room is ON");
   }
   public void startFan(){
       System.out.println("The Fan in the Room is On");
   }
   public void stopFan(){
       System.out.println("The Fan in the Room is Off");
   }
}
public class Main
{
	public static void main(String[] args) {
		SmartRoom s=new SmartRoom();
		s.switchoff();
		s.startFan();
		s.stopFan();
		s.switchOn();
	}
}


20. Most Common Interview Questions

✔ Can we create object of interface?

No.

✔ Can interface have constructor?

No.

✔ Can interface have variables?

Yes

But

public static final

✔ Can interface have static methods?

Yes (Java 8)

✔ Can interface have default methods?

Yes (Java 8)

✔ Can interface have private methods?

Yes (Java 9)

✔ Can a class implement multiple interfaces?

Yes.

✔ Difference between extends and implements?

Class → extends class

Class → implements interface

Interface → extends interface

















